This one got me thinking...
I tried different options but I wasn't able to make the variable rendering work (via ansible) by feeding the json file, I managed to figured what seems to be the "right" json provider setting but I was only able to do it directly in the task.


These two work:
  --provider="{\"type\":\"none\",\"disconnected\":true}"
  --provider='{\"type\":\"none\",\"disconnected\":true}'


This is what I got when using {{ lookup | from_json }}:
  --provider=\"{'type': 'none', 'disconnected': True}\"

This is what I got when using {{lookup | string }}:
  --provider=\"{\"type\": \"none\", \"disconnected\": true}\"

This is what I got when using {{ lookup | string }} + single quoting i.e. --provider='{{ provider_config }}':
  --provider='{\"type\": \"none\", \"disconnected\": true}'

Is the same as what's needed but does not work for some reason.

Note the True vs true, lower case was needed otherwise it won't parse it correctly. Lastly I'm using `none` because that's what I found in a test they use for disconnected envs: https://github.com/openshift/origin/blob/master/cmd/openshift-tests/provider_test.go#L225

Probably both are OK (skeleton and none) as I see they change none to skeleton: https://github.com/openshift/origin/blob/master/cmd/openshift-tests/provider.go#L73-L74

Anyway I'll make the change, drop the file and test.

-In fact, the results obtained in daily jobs and in this change are the same. If we compare this OCP-4.8 daily job (https://www.distributed-ci.io/jobs/ebc870d5-5c5f-40ad-8343-6b39eed55ab4/tests) with the passed OCP-4.8 job from this change (https://www.distributed-ci.io/jobs/bbe2929b-7bc6-4a75-ad98-a49fa42c351d/tests), the number of passed/skipped sriov tests is the same in both cases.

-I have also seen the rendering problem with the XML file uploaded, it is quite strange, in fact, but it seems that the tests whose name includes "strange" characters are not being rendered correctly. I guess this should be an issue to be reported in the openshift-kni/cnf-features-deploy
